links.title: QIAGEN announces preliminary sales and earnings
links.description: QIAGEN N.V. announces preliminary sales grew 26% to $481.3M from $382.7M in 2019. Figures much higher than outlook 16-21% sales growth announced in July.The better-than-expected results reflect both ongoing significant demand for solutions used in COVID-19 testing, as well as significantly improved customer demand trends in other areas of the portfolio from Q2.Preliminary adjusted EPS ~$0.58 - a 61% increase from adjusted EPS of $0.36 Q3 2019, at the high end of the outlook for about $0.52-0.58 given in July.
